---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import portrait from '~/assets/andreas-styltsvig.png';
const lang = 'en' as const;
---
<BaseLayout
  lang={lang}
  title="About — AStyltsvig Consulting"
  description="Andreas Sørbye Styltsvig runs AStyltsvig Consulting as a single-person practice in Copenhagen — IT consulting, software development, and AI productivity for companies."
>
  <article class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-24 md:pt-32 pb-16">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] gap-10 md:gap-16 items-center">
      <div>
        <p class="fade-in font-[var(--font-mono)] text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[var(--color-muted)]">About</p>
        <h1 class="fade-in !mt-4 max-w-[16ch]">
          One developer. <span class="grad-text">Deep focus.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="fade-in mt-8 max-w-[48ch] text-lg text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed">
          I'm Andreas Sørbye Styltsvig, and I run <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)] font-semibold">AStyltsvig Consulting</strong> as a single-person practice out of Vanløse, Copenhagen.
        </p>
      </div>
      <figure class="fade-in order-first md:order-last w-44 md:w-60 lg:w-72 justify-self-start md:justify-self-end">
        <Image
          src={portrait}
          alt="Portrait of Andreas Sørbye Styltsvig"
          widths={[320, 480, 640, 800]}
          sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 288px, (min-width: 768px) 240px, 176px"
          format="webp"
          quality={82}
          loading="eager"
          class="w-full h-auto rounded-2xl shadow-xl ring-1 ring-white/10"
        />
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class="fade-in mt-16 glass p-8 md:p-12 prose-body mx-auto">
      <p class="!mt-0">
        I've worked in IT and web development for more than a decade, and my focus is on building and maintaining software for organisations where the system needs to live for many years and hold up under actual use — not just a demo.
      </p>
      <p>
        Since late 2025 a growing part of my practice is <strong>AI productivity consulting</strong>: helping companies move from ad-hoc chatbot use to a real AI-assisted workflow that produces measurable gains. I don't sell it as theory — I use it every day on my own production systems, and I can show the difference it makes.
      </p>

      <h2>What I can help with</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Helping companies get real productivity out of AI — tools, workflows, and practices that survive production</li>
        <li>Building and maintaining web applications (typically Vue and Laravel)</li>
        <li>Migrating older sites (typically WordPress) to modern, static stacks</li>
        <li>Taking over ownership of DNS, email, and domain administration from a previous vendor</li>
        <li>Advising on technical architecture, vendor selection, and operational setup</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I don't do</h2>
      <p>
        Pure frontend design without development, SEO-as-a-service, paid advertising, or "quick fixes" on systems I don't have the chance to understand properly. I'd rather take on fewer clients and go deep with each of them.
      </p>

      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>
        I hold a <strong>Professional Bachelor's in Software Development</strong> from Copenhagen Business Academy (Cphbusiness Lyngby, 2019) and started freelancing full-time in 2020 after a year at Prolike ApS — where I was outsourced to <strong>Oticon</strong> leading a migration from Jenkins and SVN to Azure DevOps with proper CI/CD pipelines and Git-based workflows.
      </p>
      <p>
        My flagship product is the ERP system I've built and operated for <a href="https://mallard.dk" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Mallard</strong></a> since 2022 — the proving ground where I've refined how AI-assisted development actually works in sustained production. Earlier engagements include <strong>SecureLife A/S</strong>, where I led development of a secure financial platform handling insurance and pension policies for more than 2,500 employees across 200+ companies, and <a href="https://book2go.bike" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>book2go.bike</strong></a>, the real-time multilingual booking platform I built for <strong>Cycling Without Age</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>Off the clock</h2>
      <p>
        I live in Vanløse with my family and spend as much time as the Danish weather allows on my 36-foot sailboat. It's where I do my best thinking about systems that need to hold up over time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
